# 0. Configure Log Forwarding

Before you can use the kit, you'll need to get logs flowing from your Fortinet FortiGate / FortiOS 7.6.6 device into Gravwell. Our recommended method is via syslog forwarding. Gravwell can receive syslog data using the Simple Relay ingester.

An integration guide is available on [this documentation page](https://docs.gravwell.io/integrations/network/fortinet).

Once the changes have been committed/applied, logs should begin flowing into Gravwell. You can check by running the following queries:

```gravwell
tag=fortinet-traffic
| limit 20
```

```gravwell
tag=fortinet-utm
| limit 20
```

```gravwell
tag=fortinet-system
| limit 20
```

```gravwell
tag=fortinet-events
| limit 20
```

If any results appear, logs are coming in properly as expected.

